name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)

main.name: Szarekh, the Silent King
main.oracle_text:
Flying
My Will Be Done — Whenever Szarekh, the Silent King attacks, mill three cards. You may put an artifact creature card or Vehicle card from among the cards milled this way into your hand.

card.name: Mind Stone
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}, {T}, Sacrifice Mind Stone: Draw a card.
card.flavor_text: During biotransference, the Necrontyr lost almost all individuality. What little remained was imprisoned within a living metal form.

card.name: Mask of Memory
card.oracle_text:
Whenever equipped creature deals combat damage to a player, you may draw two cards. If you do, discard a card.
Equip {1} ({1}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Lychguard
card.oracle_text: Guardian Protocols — {3}{B}, Sacrifice Lychguard: Return all legendary creature cards from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text:
"Only the deathless can truly comprehend the burden of unfailing loyalty."
—Vargard Obyron of the Sautekh Dynasty

card.name: Lokhust Heavy Destroyer
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Enmitic Exterminator — When Lokhust Heavy Destroyer enters, each player sacrifices a creature.
Unearth {5}{B}{B}{B} ({5}{B}{B}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Living Death
card.oracle_text: Each player exiles all creature cards from their graveyard, then sacrifices all creatures they control, then puts all cards they exiled this way onto the battlefield.

card.name: Illuminor Szeras
card.oracle_text: Secrets of the Soul — {T}, Sacrifice another creature: Add an amount of {B} equal to the sacrificed creature's mana value.
card.flavor_text: "Immortality is not quite the same as invulnerability, but it is close enough."

card.name: Hexmark Destroyer
card.oracle_text:
Multi-threat Eliminator — Hexmark Destroyer can't be blocked except by six or more creatures.
Unearth {4}{B}{B} ({4}{B}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Hedron Archive
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}{C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Hedron Archive: Draw two cards.
card.flavor_text: The vaults of the Necron Dynasties contain all manner of esoteric artifacts, most forged long before many of the younger races even existed.

card.name: Go for the Throat
card.oracle_text: Destroy target nonartifact creature.
card.flavor_text:
"Pray that night is upon us, for if this twilight is the work of the Necrons, we are all dead men."
—Address by Lieutenant Krakow prior to the Bloodmoon Massacres

card.name: Ghost Ark
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Repair Barge — Whenever Ghost Ark becomes crewed, each artifact creature card in your graveyard gains unearth {3} until end of turn.
Crew 2 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 2 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

card.name: Gilded Lotus
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add three mana of any one color.
card.flavor_text:
"The ancient Necron race has achieved this pinnacle of elegance through their relentless pursuit of utility."
—Tech-Priest Darvin, executed for heresy 1256998.M41

card.name: Endless Atlas
card.oracle_text: {2}, {T}: Draw a card. Activate only if you control three or more lands with the same name.
card.flavor_text:
"While we slept, our inferiors infested the worlds that belong to us. Now, we awaken once more."
—Szarekh, the Silent King

card.name: Dread Return
card.oracle_text:
Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
Flashback—Sacrifice three creatures. (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
card.flavor_text:
"Bolters, flamers, plasma—we hit the xenos with everything, and it just kept coming."
—Captain Uriel Ventris

card.name: Desert of the Glorified
card.oracle_text:
Desert of the Glorified enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
Cycling {1}{B} ({1}{B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
card.flavor_text: On countless frontier worlds, below silica sand, blasted chalk, or bubbling marsh, slumbering Necrons await.

card.name: Defile
card.oracle_text: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn for each Swamp you control.
card.flavor_text:
"Agresto, bring up the rear . . . Agresto?"
—Sergeant Dremark Eigen, last words

card.name: Darkness
card.oracle_text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.
card.flavor_text: By the physical laws of the universe, darkness is merely the absence of light. Necrons can harness the power of other dimensions, where darkness is tangible and moldable.

card.name: Cryptek
card.oracle_text: {1}{B}, {T}: Choose another target artifact creature you control. When that creature dies this turn, return it to the battlefield tapped under your control.
card.flavor_text: There are those who draw false comparisons between the tech-magi of the Adeptus Mechanicus and the xenotechnologists of the necron race. There can be no mercy for such heretics.

card.name: Cryptothrall
card.oracle_text: Protector — Other artifact creatures you control have hexproof.
card.flavor_text: Bound to a cryptek, the cryptothrall exists for one reason: to defend its master to the death.

card.name: Cranial Plating
card.flavor_text: The flesh of the Necrontyr is a memory so distant as to be nearly mythical.

card.name: Convergence of Dominion
card.oracle_text:
Dynastic Command Node — As long as you control your commander, activated abilities of cards in your graveyard cost {2} less to activate. This effect can't reduce the mana in that ability's activation cost to less than one mana.
Translocation Protocols — {3}, {T}: Mill three cards.

card.name: Commander's Sphere
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
Sacrifice Commander's Sphere: Draw a card.
card.flavor_text: Within it rests the power of a sun, and none of the warmth.

card.name: Chronomancer
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Atomic Transmutation — {1}, {T}, Sacrifice another artifact: Draw a card.
Unearth {2}{B} ({2}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Canoptek Wraith
card.oracle_text:
Wraith Form — Canoptek Wraith can't be blocked.
Transdimensional Scout — When Canoptek Wraith deals combat damage to a player, you may pay {3} and sacrifice it. If you do, choose a land you control. Then search your library for up to two basic land cards which have the same name as the chosen land, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

card.name: Canoptek Tomb Sentinel
card.oracle_text:
Vigilance
Exile Cannon — When Canoptek Tomb Sentinel enters from a graveyard, exile up to one target nonland permanent.
Unearth {7} ({7}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Canoptek Spyder
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Fabricator Claw Array — Whenever another nontoken artifact creature or Vehicle you control enters, draw a card.

card.name: Caged Sun
card.oracle_text:
As Caged Sun enters, choose a color.
Creatures you control of the chosen color get +1/+1.
Whenever a land's ability causes you to add one or more mana of the chosen color, add one additional mana of that color.

card.name: Beacon of Unrest
card.oracle_text: Put target artifact or creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. Shuffle Beacon of Unrest into its owner's library.
card.flavor_text:
"Rise and serve me once more."
—Trazyn the Infinite

card.name: Barren Moor
card.oracle_text:
Barren Moor enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
Cycling {B} ({B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
card.flavor_text: Millennia of constant warfare have left many planets with very little worth fighting over.

card.name: Arcane Signet
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: All Necrons bear the mark of the Triarch, a brand upon their living-metal skin that binds them to their dynasty.

card.name: Anrakyr the Traveller
card.oracle_text: Lord of the Pyrrhian Legions — Whenever Anrakyr the Traveller attacks, you may cast an artifact spell from your hand or graveyard by paying life equal to its mana value rather than paying its mana cost.
card.flavor_text: "Though it may take an eternity, I will see the myriad dynasties united once more."

card.name: Night Scythe
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Invasion Beams — When Night Scythe enters, create a 2/2 black Necron Warrior artifact creature token.
Crew 2 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 2 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

card.name: Their Number Is Legion
card.oracle_text:
Create X tapped 2/2 black Necron Warrior artifact creature tokens, then you gain life equal to the number of artifacts you control. Exile Their Number Is Legion.
You may cast Their Number Is Legion from your graveyard.

card.name: Biotransference
card.oracle_text:
Creatures you control are artifacts in addition to their other types. The same is true for creature spells you control and creature cards you own that aren't on the battlefield.
Whenever you cast an artifact spell, you lose 1 life and create a 2/2 black Necron Warrior artifact creature token.

card.name: Necron Monolith
card.oracle_text:
Flying, indestructible
Eternity Gate — Whenever Necron Monolith attacks, mill three cards. For each creature card milled this way, create a 2/2 black Necron Warrior artifact creature token.
Crew 4 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 4 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

card.name: Royal Warden
card.oracle_text:
Phalanx Commander — When Royal Warden enters, create two tapped 2/2 black Necron Warrior artifact creature tokens.
Unearth {3}{B} ({3}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Canoptek Scarab Swarm
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Feeder Mandibles — When Canoptek Scarab Swarm enters, exile target player's graveyard. For each artifact or land card exiled this way, create a 1/1 colorless Insect artifact creature token with flying.

card.name: Flayed One
card.oracle_text:
Lifelink
Flesh Flayer — When Flayed One enters, mill three cards.
card.flavor_text: Those suspected of carrying the flayer curse are summarily banished, lest the corruption spread to other Necrons.

card.name: Trazyn the Infinite
card.oracle_text:
Deathtouch
Prismatic Gallery — As long as Trazyn the Infinite is on the battlefield, it has all activated abilities of all artifact cards in your graveyard.
card.flavor_text: The Archaeovist of the Solemnace Galleries will not rest until every treasure in the galaxy is safely within his clutches.

card.name: Imotekh the Stormlord
card.oracle_text:
Phaeron — Whenever one or more artifact cards leave your graveyard, create two 2/2 black Necron Warrior artifact creature tokens.
Grand Strategist — At the beginning of combat on your turn, another target artifact creature you control gets +2/+2 and gains menace until end of turn.

card.name: Mutilate
card.oracle_text: All creatures get -1/-1 until end of turn for each Swamp you control.
card.flavor_text: "You mortals turn to dust in the blink of an eye. I only expedite your fate."

card.name: Myriad Landscape
card.oracle_text:
Myriad Landscape enters tapped.
{T}: Add {C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Myriad Landscape: Search your library for up to two basic land cards that share a land type, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

card.name: Mystic Forge
card.oracle_text:
You may look at the top card of your library any time.
You may cast artifact spells and colorless spells from the top of your library.
{T}, Pay 1 life: Exile the top card of your library.

card.name: Necron Deathmark
card.oracle_text:
Flash
Synaptic Disintegrator — When Necron Deathmark enters, destroy up to one target creature and target player mills three cards.

card.name: Necron Overlord
card.oracle_text: Relentless March — {X}, {T}, Tap X untapped artifacts you control: Target opponent loses X life.
card.flavor_text: "This galaxy once knelt before us, and it will do so again."

card.name: Out of the Tombs
card.oracle_text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, put two eon counters on Out of the Tombs, then mill cards equal to the number of eon counters on it.
If you would draw a card while your library has no cards in it, instead return a creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. If you can't, you lose the game.

card.name: Plasmancer
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Dynastic Advisor — When Plasmancer enters, search your library for a basic Swamp card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Masters of dimensional dissonance, singularity manipulation, and countless other technologies, plasmancers are terrifying to behold.

card.name: Polluted Mire
card.oracle_text:
Polluted Mire enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
Cycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
card.flavor_text: As the continent sank over the course of eons, the tomb complex slowly flooded. The sleeping Necrons, their stasis crypts corrupted, never awoke.

card.name: Psychomancer
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Harbinger of Despair — Whenever Psychomancer or another nontoken artifact you control is put into a graveyard from the battlefield or is put into exile from the battlefield, target opponent loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.

card.name: Reliquary Tower
card.oracle_text:
You have no maximum hand size.
{T}: Add {C}.
card.flavor_text:
"Let the others bicker over their little worlds and stars. I have an empire of knowledge, and it encompasses all others."
—Trazyn the Infinite

card.name: Resurrection Orb
card.oracle_text:
Equipped creature has lifelink.
Whenever equipped creature dies, return that card to the battlefield under its owner's control at the beginning of the next end step.
Equip {4} ({4}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Sautekh Immortal
card.oracle_text:
Flash
Elite Troops — Sautekh Immortal enters with a +1/+1 counter on it for each creature that died this turn.
card.flavor_text:
"Nothing clears a battlefield like a Deathstrike missile. Wait. Is something moving out there?"
—Commmander Zander At'lan, Tallarn 115th Armoured Regiment

card.name: Sceptre of Eternal Glory
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add one mana of any color.
{T}: Add three mana of any one color. Activate only if you control three or more lands with the same name.
card.flavor_text: It burns with the very fire that doomed Szarekh's species, and channels it to devastate his foes.

card.name: Sculpting Steel
card.oracle_text: You may have Sculpting Steel enter as a copy of any artifact on the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: Necrodermis, the living metal from which all Necrons are made, is endlessly adaptive.

card.name: Shard of the Nightbringer
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Drain Life — When Shard of the Nightbringer enters, if you cast it, target opponent loses half their life, rounded up. You gain life equal to the life lost this way.
card.flavor_text:
"Aza'gorod, the Nightbringer. The embodiment of death. A killer of stars and of worlds."
—Illuminor Szeras

card.name: Shard of the Void Dragon
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Spear of the Void Dragon — Whenever Shard of the Void Dragon attacks, each opponent sacrifices a nonland permanent.
Matter Absorption — Whenever an artifact is put into a graveyard from the battlefield or is put into exile from the battlefield, put two +1/+1 counters on Shard of the Void Dragon.

card.name: Skorpekh Destroyer
card.oracle_text:
Deathtouch
Hyperphase Threshers — Whenever an artifact you control enters, Skorpekh Destroyer gains first strike until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: Nothing can override the hard-wired desire to kill that empowers these rage-driven Necrons.

card.name: Skorpekh Lord
card.oracle_text:
Menace
Command Protocols — Other artifact creatures you control get +1/+0 and have menace.
Unearth {2}{B} ({2}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text:
"Once, the C'tan sought to rule us. Now it is they who serve us, their shards powering our great machines."
—Szarekh, the Silent King

card.name: Technomancer
card.oracle_text: When Technomancer enters, mill three cards, then return any number of artifact creature cards with total mana value 6 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield.
card.flavor_text:
"Witchcraft or technology, it is blasphemous, and it must be stopped."
—Inquisitor Greyfax

card.name: Their Name Is Death
card.oracle_text: Destroy all nonartifact creatures.
card.flavor_text:
"When the Silent King saw what had been done, he knew at last the true nature of the C'tan, and the doom they had wrought in his name."
—*The Book of Mournful Night*

card.name: The War in Heaven
card.oracle_text:
(As this Saga enters and after your draw step, add a lore counter. Sacrifice after III.)
I — You draw three cards and you lose 3 life.
II — Mill three cards.
III — Choose up to three target creature cards with total mana value 8 or less in your graveyard. Return each of them to the battlefield with a necrodermis counter on it. They're artifacts in addition to their other types.

card.name: Thought Vessel
card.oracle_text:
You have no maximum hand size.
{T}: Add {C}.
card.flavor_text: Before the Great Sleep, the Necrons knew every corner of the galaxy, as only the ultimate conquerors could.

card.name: Tomb Blade
Tomb Fortress
card.oracle_text:
Tomb Fortress enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
{2}{B}{B}{B}, {T}, Exile Tomb Fortress: Mill four cards, then return a creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. Activate only as a sorcery.

card.name: Triarch Praetorian
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Dynastic Codes — When Triarch Praetorian enters from a graveyard, you draw two cards and you lose 2 life.
Unearth {4}{B} ({4}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Triarch Stalker
card.oracle_text:
Targeting Relay — At the beginning of combat on your turn, choose an opponent.
Creatures attacking the last chosen player have menace.
card.flavor_text:
"Scour this world of these impudent trespassers!"
—Lord Traedrekkh of the Sekemtar Dynasty

card.name: Unstable Obelisk
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{7}, {T}, Sacrifice Unstable Obelisk: Destroy target permanent.
card.flavor_text:
"It's a lifeless ruin of some long-lost race. What is there to fear?"
—Commissar Gadholm

card.name: Vault of Whispers
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {B}.
card.flavor_text: Heretic cultures came to planet Sovereign in search of resources and precious artifacts. They found something else.

card.name: Wayfarer's Bauble
card.oracle_text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice Wayfarer's Bauble: Search your library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Anrakyr the Traveler awoke from his slumber with a singular goal: to rebuild a united Necron galaxy.

card.oracle_text:

My Will Be Done — Whenever Szarekh, the Silent King attacks, mill three cards. You may put an artifact creature card or Vehicle card from among the cards milled this way into your hand.
